#. type: Title =
#: Tool-ZoneMapper-Exposure.markdown.txt:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "ZoneMapper: Adjusting exposure\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-ZoneMapper-Exposure.markdown.txt:5
msgid "[4 of 8](Tool-ZoneMapper-Contrast.html)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-ZoneMapper-Exposure.markdown.txt:8
msgid ""
"One of several adjustments you can make to your photo using the ZoneMapper "
"tool is exposure."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title -
#: Tool-ZoneMapper-Exposure.markdown.txt:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "To increase the exposure of your photo:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-ZoneMapper-Exposure.markdown.txt:13
msgid "![image](images/Button-ZoneMapper.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1.  '
#: Tool-ZoneMapper-Exposure.markdown.txt:24
msgid ""
"Click the ZoneMapper tool button in the [tool bar](Tools-Editing.html). (A "
"new ZoneMapper tool will appear at the top of the [tool "
"stack](Tool_Stack.html).)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2.  '
#: Tool-ZoneMapper-Exposure.markdown.txt:24
msgid ""
"Starting from the first zone, move the mouse downwards along the zones in "
"the ZoneMapper until you find a zone that shows significant highlighting in "
"the [ZoneFinder](ZoneFinder.html)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3.  '
#: Tool-ZoneMapper-Exposure.markdown.txt:24
msgid ""
"Click above that zone. A *zone lock* will appear (a thin, blue line with a "
"little 'X' at its right)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '4.  '
#: Tool-ZoneMapper-Exposure.markdown.txt:24
msgid ""
"Drag the zone lock upwards. As you do so, your photo's exposure will "
"increase."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-ZoneMapper-Exposure.markdown.txt:29
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"      --------------------------------------------------------- -- "
"--------------------------------------------------------\n"
"      (a) before                                                   (b) "
"after\n"
"      ![image](images/Tool-ZoneMapper-Exposure-before-en.png)      "
"![image](images/Tool-ZoneMapper-Exposure-after-en.png)\n"
"      --------------------------------------------------------- -- "
"--------------------------------------------------------\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-ZoneMapper-Exposure.markdown.txt:36
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"5.  Optionally:\n"
"    -   Create a mask using [regions](Regions.html).\n"
"    -   Select a different [blend mode](Blend_Modes.html).\n"
"    -   Adjust the [Opacity slider](Tool_Anatomy.html#Opacity).\n"
"    -   Make a [color/luminosity](Color_Luminosity_Selection.html)\n"
"        selection.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '6.  '
#: Tool-ZoneMapper-Exposure.markdown.txt:38
msgid "To delete a zone lock, click the little 'X' at its right."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-ZoneMapper-Exposure.markdown.txt:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "    ![image](images/Tool-ZoneMapper-X.png)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-ZoneMapper-Exposure.markdown.txt:43
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Note:** To decrease the exposure of you photo, create a zone lock\n"
"above the first zone and drag it downwards.\n"
msgstr ""

